.\" pdrx.1 - man page for pdrx
.\" Portable Dynamic Reproducible gnu/linuX - reproducible Linux system setup
.\" Use: groff -man -Tutf8 pdrx.1 | less
.TH pdrx 1 "2026-07-15" "pdrx 1.9.6" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pdrx \- Portable Dynamic Reproducible gnu/linuX: reproducible Linux system setup with declarative package config
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pdrx
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pdrx
(Portable Dynamic Reproducible gnu/linuX) is a pure Bash tool for fully reproducible Linux system setups. It has no Nix or other external dependency and works on Debian, Ubuntu, Fedora, Arch, openSUSE, and other major distributions.
.PP
You install and remove packages imperatively (e.g. \fBpdrx install vim\fR). pdrx records each package together with the \fIpackage manager\fR used (apt, flatpak, cargo, etc.) in a declarative config file. When you run \fBpdrx apply\fR on another machine, it installs the same packages via the same package managers, giving you a reproducible environment.
.PP
Supported package managers: \fBapt\fR, \fBdnf\fR, \fByum\fR, \fBpacman\fR, \fBzypper\fR, \fBbrew\fR, \fBflatpak\fR, \fBsnap\fR, \fBcargo\fR, and \fBwinget\fR. pdrx auto-detects which of these are available on the system.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help message and exit.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version information and exit.
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Reduce output verbosity.
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-debug\fR
Enable verbose debug output.
.TP
\fB\-y\fR, \fB\-\-yes\fR
Answer yes to all confirmation prompts automatically.
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show what would be done without making changes.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR \fIDIR\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR \fIDIR\fR
Use \fIDIR\fR as pdrx home directory (default: \fI$HOME/.pdrx\fR).
.TP
\fB\-\-install\fR
Install pdrx to \fI~/.local/bin\fR and add to PATH.
.TP
\fB\-\-pm\fR \fIPM\fR
Specify package manager (apt, dnf, yum, pacman, zypper, brew, flatpak, snap, cargo, winget).
.TP
\fB\-\-pin\fR[=\fIVERSION\fR]
Pin package to specific version (used with install).
.TP
\fB\-\-parallel\fR
Search across package managers in parallel (used with search).
.SH COMMANDS
.SS init
Initialize pdrx. Creates config directory structure, packages file, sources file, systemd file, and state files. Also exports current desktop state if supported.
.PP
\fBpdrx init\fR
.SS status
Show current status: config path, detected package managers, packages/sources/units counts, hook presence, and backup count.
.PP
\fBpdrx status\fR
.SS doctor (fsck)
Audit declared config against actual system state. Checks: missing declared packages, undeclared manually-installed packages (drift), tracked dotfile symlink health, and config layout validity. Alias: fsck.
.PP
\fBpdrx doctor\fR
.br
\fBpdrx fsck\fR
.SS install
Install packages and record them in declarative config. Supports version pinning and explicit PM selection.
.PP
\fBpdrx install\fR [\fB\-\-pin\fR[=\fIVERSION\fR]] \fIpkg\fR [\fIpkg\fR...]
.br
\fBpdrx install \-\-pm\fR \fIPM\fR [\fB\-\-pin\fR[=\fIVERSION\fR]] \fIpkg\fR [\fIpkg\fR...]
.SS remove
Remove packages from system and declarative config. Supports dry-run.
.PP
\fBpdrx remove\fR [\fB\-n\fR] \fIpkg\fR [\fIpkg\fR...]
.SS list
List all packages in declarative config, grouped by package manager.
.PP
\fBpdrx list\fR
.SS search
Search for packages across available package managers. Supports parallel search.
.PP
\fBpdrx search\fR [\fB\-\-parallel\fR] \fITERM\fR [\fIPM_NUM\fR ...]
.SS apply
Apply declarative config: install all packages, add sources, enable systemd units, apply dotfiles, and restore desktop settings.
.PP
\fBpdrx apply\fR [\fB\-n\fR]
.SS track
Track a dotfile (e.g. \fI~/.bashrc\fR). Creates symlink from original to pdrx copy. Paths outside $HOME are rejected.
.PP
\fBpdrx track\fR \fIPATH\fR [\fIPATH\fR...]
.SS untrack
Untrack dotfiles: replace symlinks with real files and remove from config.
.PP
\fBpdrx untrack\fR [\fB\-\-all\fR|\fB\-\-dir\fR \fIDIR\fR] \fIPATH\fR [\fIPATH\fR...]
.br
\fBpdrx untrack \-\-all\fR
.SS backup
Create timestamped backup of entire pdrx home directory.
.PP
\fBpdrx backup\fR [\fILABEL\fR]
.SS restore
Restore pdrx home from backup.
.PP
\fBpdrx restore\fR [\fB\-y\fR] [\fBBACKUP_NAME\fR]
.br
\fBpdrx restore \-\-list\fR
.SS clean
Remove old backups, keeping only recent ones.
.PP
\fBpdrx clean\fR [\fB\-\-keep\fR \fIN\fR]
.SS history
Show audit log of state-changing actions (JSON-lines format).
.PP
\fBpdrx history\fR [\fIN\fR]
.SS source
Manage repository/PPA/third-party sources.
.PP
\fBpdrx source\fR \fIURL\fR [\fISRC_NAME\fR]
.br
\fBpdrx source \-\-remove\fR \fISRC_NAME\fR
.br
\fBpdrx source \-\-list\fR
.SS systemd
Manage systemd unit enablement.
.PP
\fBpdrx systemd\fR [\fB\-\-user\fR] \fIUNIT\fR
.br
\fBpdrx systemd \-\-remove\fR [\fB\-\-user\fR] \fIUNIT\fR
.br
\fBpdrx systemd \-\-list\fR
.SS desktop
Export or import desktop environment settings.
.PP
\fBpdrx desktop export\fR [\fB\-\-skip\fR]
.br
\fBpdrx desktop import\fR [\fB\-\-merge\fR|\fB\-\-replace\fR]
.SS sync
Sync declarative config with actual system state (records manually-installed packages).
.PP
\fBpdrx sync\fR
.SS rollback
Rollback to previous state before last apply.
.PP
\fBpdrx rollback\fR [\fB\-y\fR]
.SS upgrade
Upgrade all packages in declarative config to latest versions.
.PP
\fBpdrx upgrade\fR
.SS self-update
Update pdrx itself to latest release from GitHub with SHA256 verification.
.PP
\fBpdrx self-update\fR
.SS export
Export pdrx config as tarball or Ansible playbook.
.PP
\fBpdrx export\fR [\fIFILE\fR.tar.gz]
.br
\fBpdrx export \-\-ansible\fR \fIDIR\fR
.SS import
Import pdrx config from tarball.
.PP
\fBpdrx import\fR \fIFILE\fR.tar.gz
.SS destroy
Completely remove pdrx: restore dotfiles, remove PDRX_HOME, remove binary and manpage.
.PP
\fBpdrx destroy\fR [\fB\-y\fR|\fB\-n\fR]
.SH CONFIG LAYOUT
.PP
~/.pdrx/
.br
├── config/
.br
│   ├── packages.conf          # Declarative packages
.br
│   ├── sources.conf           # Repository/PPA sources
.br
│   ├── systemd.conf           # Enabled systemd units
.br
│   ├── dotfiles/              # Tracked dotfile copies
.br
│   ├── desktop-export/        # Exported DE settings
.br
│   └── hooks/                 # Post-apply hooks
.br
├── backups/                   # Timestamped backups
.br
└── state/
.br
    ├── initialized            # Initialization marker
.br
    ├── tracked-dotfiles     # List of tracked paths
.br
    ├── generations          # Backup timestamps
.br
    └── pdrx.log             # Audit log (JSON-lines)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBPDRX_HOME\fR
Path to pdrx home directory. Default: \fI$HOME/.pdrx\fR.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fR
Success.
.TP
\fB1\fR
General error.
